gomodel:SYNGO_1465  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Guanylyl cyclase B1/3 is a subunit of soluble Guanylyl cyclase that forms a heterodimer with an alpha subunits and is involved in signal transduction downstream of NO. The authors used immunocytochmistry and confocal microscopy in the CA1 region of the hippocampus to show colocalization of Guanylyl cyclase B1/3 with the presynaptic marker synpatophysin.\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\nFig.3: Authors note: \"Although the limited resolution of light microscopy prevents definite conclusions, these data are consistent with the hypothesis that sGC concentrates in axon terminals, whereas NOS-I concentrates in postsynaptic densities.\"\nFig.6: \" Quantitative EM of randomly selected asymmetric synapses in the stratum radiatum confirmed that gold particles coding for NOS-I were predominantly postsynaptic, concentrating just cytoplasmic to the postsynaptic membrane, whereas particles coding for sGCβ were predominantly presynaptic, concentrating ~15-25 nm cytoplasmic to the presynaptic membrane (Fig. 6 C).\". Experimental description: Mixed species are used: \"All procedures related to the care and treatment of animals were in accordance with institutional and National Institutes of Health guidelines. Ten male Sprague Dawley rats (200-350 gm; Charles River, Raleigh, NC) and eight male mice..\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1465" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

